> Oops, seems after reverting this patch I ran into the exact same problem.
It was hard to understand how the patch could cause a kernel crash. The only significant change
is adding the purge_kernel_dcache_page_addr call in flush_anon_page.Â  It uses the pdc instruction
to invalidate the kernel mapping.Â  Assuming pdc is actually implemented as described in the architecture
book, it doesn't write back to memory at priority 0.Â  It just invalidates the addressed cache line.

My 6.8.9 build is still going after 2 hours and 42 minutes...

>
> First the failing package is actually perl XS-Parse-Keyword, not the actual perl interpreter.Â  Didn't have serial console hooked up to check 
